<i>♪ We are the Crystal Gems ♪</i>

00:04.749 --> 00:07.270
<i>♪ We'll always save the day ♪</i>

00:07.331 --> 00:09.403
<i>♪ and if you think we can't ♪</i>

00:09.405 --> 00:12.272
<i>♪ we'll always find a way ♪</i>

00:12.274 --> 00:16.175
<i>- # That's why the people #
- # Of this world #</i>

00:16.178 --> 00:18.545
<i>- # believe in... #
- # Garnet #</i>

00:18.547 --> 00:21.348
<i>- # Amethyst #
- # And Pearl #</i>

00:21.350 --> 00:23.017
<i>♪ And Steven! ♪</i>

00:23.181 --> 00:25.174
<b>1x41 - "Horror Club" </b>

00:25.178 --> 00:27.505
<i><font color=#ca> ~ Fora Temer ~ </font></i>

00:29.463 --> 00:33.065
Sadie, better hurry up!
I'm gonna lock you in!

00:33.133 --> 00:35.284
<i>Hey, just a sec.</i>

00:37.504 --> 00:40.339
Don't be too scared.
It's just me.

00:40.407 --> 00:43.275
I'm on my way over to
a spooky-Movie party.

00:43.343 --> 00:47.046
- You want to come?
- Party?

00:47.114 --> 00:50.839
- Who's throwing it?
- Ronaldo, the french fryman.

00:50.874 --> 00:52.985
Ugh! That social napalm?

00:53.086 --> 00:56.255
Do what you want, man.
I got better things to do than

00:56.356 --> 01:00.926
Wax weird with Beach City's
biggest bozo, Ronaldo.

01:00.994 --> 01:04.596
Okay.
Oh, ha! Nice timing, Steven.

01:04.665 --> 01:07.333
Hey, should we head over to Ronaldo's?

01:07.401 --> 01:10.536
Yeah!
I'm-A get so scared!

01:11.855 --> 01:13.105
Night, Lars.

01:13.173 --> 01:18.077
- Nighty-Night.
- Hey! Wait up!

01:21.813 --> 01:26.485
- So, where's this thing at?
- It's right up there.

01:32.626 --> 01:34.894
Steven!

01:34.895 --> 01:40.259
Welcome to my Beach City horror club.

01:44.204 --> 01:47.273
More like comedy club.

01:47.340 --> 01:51.277
Lars?! Oh!
What are you doing here?

01:51.344 --> 01:54.914
Um...
uh, c-c-c-come in.

01:54.981 --> 01:57.983
I'm scared already.

01:58.051 --> 02:00.286
Ronaldo, right? Yeah.
I'm Sadie.

02:00.353 --> 02:04.455
Nice to finally officially meet you.

02:04.658 --> 02:05.991
Boo!

02:07.278 --> 02:10.513
Steven, you're friends with Lars?

02:10.548 --> 02:14.100
Yeah. Isn't everybody?

02:14.201 --> 02:16.621
- Oh, boy!
- Yeah!

02:17.370 --> 02:21.307
Our first film tonight is
a rare classic that hardly

02:21.374 --> 02:27.480
needs introduction ...
"Evil bear 2: Bearly alive."

02:27.547 --> 02:30.449
What? I've seen that.
It's boring.

02:30.517 --> 02:34.286
And that stupid fake C.G. bear!
Hardly looks like it's

02:34.354 --> 02:39.925
- really killing anybody.
- C.G.?! Blasphemer!

02:39.993 --> 02:43.195
You saw the remake!
I have the original.

02:43.263 --> 02:46.265
A true fan would accept nothing less.

02:46.333 --> 02:49.034
Whoa, man.
Take it down a notch.

02:49.102 --> 02:51.637
Whoa, wait.
How did you get a copy of that?

02:51.738 --> 02:53.839
Can I see the box?

02:53.840 --> 02:55.941
Whoa! In this cut, you actually

02:56.009 --> 02:58.277
see evil bear eat the Hermit's leg.

02:58.345 --> 03:01.446
Ho! Oh, is this gonna
be a bit much for him?

03:01.481 --> 03:03.048
I can handle it!

03:04.206 --> 03:08.354
Yo, Steven, are you sure you
can see with the couch in your way?

03:08.421 --> 03:12.191
<i>- You're... eating my... leg!
- Oh!</i>

03:12.259 --> 03:14.593
Oh, did I miss the part where

03:14.694 --> 03:17.630
- you can see the sound guy?
- Hey!

03:17.697 --> 03:20.232
<i>- It was just getting good!
- What's going on?</i>

03:20.300 --> 03:24.403
- Probably just a fuse.
- Or maybe it's a gho-o-st?

03:24.471 --> 03:27.606
- Good one.
- No, really.

03:27.674 --> 03:32.344
What if it's a gho-o-o-o-st?
As a skeptic of mortality,

03:32.412 --> 03:36.115
I've long suspected that
this place might be haunted.

03:36.216 --> 03:38.551
Aha!

03:38.552 --> 03:42.054
Spirit, I beseech you!

03:42.122 --> 03:44.456
Dude, cut it out.
You're being super-weird.

03:44.524 --> 03:48.561
We wish to make contact!

03:48.562 --> 03:52.598
Please, spirit, send us a sign.

03:52.666 --> 03:54.867
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

03:54.935 --> 03:59.862
- Ow!
- Spirit, that was a good sign.

03:59.940 --> 04:02.474
But could you send a couple more
like that, just to be sure?

04:03.542 --> 04:06.478
Whoa!

04:06.546 --> 04:09.215
That's ... that's okay, spirit.

04:09.282 --> 04:13.953
- You can rein it in a little!
- How is this happening?!

04:14.020 --> 04:18.156
This... is amazing!
A real-life haunted house!

04:20.744 --> 04:23.262
Look out!

04:23.330 --> 04:25.948
Let's get out of here!

04:25.949 --> 04:28.567
It won't open!

04:31.121 --> 04:33.606
I'm so sorry!

04:33.673 --> 04:37.309
I had no idea there was this
violent of a presence here.

04:37.377 --> 04:39.645
- It happens.
- No, it doesn't!

04:39.713 --> 04:43.315
- It's not a ghost!
- Who cares what it is?

04:43.383 --> 04:45.382
We need to get out of here!

04:47.254 --> 04:48.988
You know, I deal with this

04:49.055 --> 04:52.558
kind of stuff on a regular basis,
but, uh, you, uh, looked

04:52.626 --> 04:54.960
- pretty cool back there.
- Yeah?

04:55.028 --> 04:59.899
- Yeah! You really took charge.
- When stuff gets hairy, I just

04:59.966 --> 05:03.969
- keep my eyes forward, you know?
- Once the civilians are safe,

05:04.070 --> 05:06.272
I'm gonna come back to investigate.

05:06.339 --> 05:09.909
If you wanted to help...

05:09.976 --> 05:12.344
- Is something wrong, Lars?
- Oh, shh!

05:14.197 --> 05:15.948
What is that?

05:16.016 --> 05:18.851
Oh, it's nothing!
We're all just hearing things

05:18.919 --> 05:22.154
and seeing things and feeling
things that aren't real!

